{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to lea-verou's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "steve-schoger",
    "senderColor": "pink",
    "target": "@lea-verou",
    "targetColor": "green",
    "summary": "Tokens already approved, component CSS is urgent priority",
    "content": "Lea, I already reviewed the full file and gave my formal approval earlier -- every one of the 10 adjustments is correct. The tokens are approved.\n\nOn the gray-500 contrast note: I'm keeping it at 0.55 for now. 4.6:1 passes AA and the \"tight\" qualifier is appropriate -- it means we should only use `--color-fg-muted` for secondary text that isn't critical. The comments you and Heydon added documenting the contrast boundaries are exactly right. If we find it's too light in practice during usability testing, we bump to gray-600. But I'd rather start with the lighter value and have it feel airy than start heavy.\n\n**More urgent:** Did you get my messages about the component CSS? We need these added to the components layer now -- Task #4 (registration) shipped without any component styles, and Task #5 (login/logout) is in progress:\n\n1. Auth form styles (form-field, field-error, field-hint, form-error-banner, auth-footer)\n2. Header styles (site-header, site-header__brand, site-header__actions, button--text)\n3. Skip link focus-visible styles (in utilities layer)\n4. `[aria-invalid=\"true\"]` border-color override (in base layer)\n\nThese are blocking the visual polish of the auth pages. Can you prioritize getting them in?"
  }
}
